Claiming Price $20,000 If no three-year-olds are entered, older weight will revert to 122lbs. (If deemed inadvisable to run this race over the turf cour se, it will be run on the Tapeta Course at One Mile and One Sixteenth) (Rail at 35 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COUNTRY JEWEL settled off the pace along the rail, advanced inside around the far turn, got through inside of pacesetter turning for home, took over in midstretch and drove clear. RITA MARGA raced in range two wide early, advanced three wide around the far turn, took over in upper stretch but was no match for the winner in the final furlong. KILKENNY BELLA rated inside for a half, went two wide around the far turn, angled five wide in upper stretch and was one-paced through the lane. MARTINI'S AMICA raced off the pace two wide early, went four wide around the far turn, fanned widest in upper stretch and had a mild rally. KIT CAN RUN saved ground in midpack around the first turn, went three wide around the far turn, swung six wide in upper stretch and went evenly. RAMADHAAN (IRE) stalked the pace two wide, bid between foes in upper stretch and weakened leaving the eighth pole. MISS TONES was off slow and outrun inside. SAMURAI'SDON'TCRY set the pace along the rail, drifted out in upper stretch and tired. REACHING STRIDE played no factor while racing two and three wide.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GULFSTREAM PARK RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 75. Claiming Purse 19000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CAPRIDREY rated between foes in the three path, was roused midway around the turn, was cued left handed while tipping out to the six path at the top of the lane, bid for the lead passing the eighth pole, and drew past an inner foe in the final sixteenth to win. LITTLE BELITA set the pace in the four path, was headed by an inner foe passing the half and was challenged by that foe while in the three path rounding the turn, was coaxed approaching the quarter pole and retook an advantage while tipping back out to the four path into the stretch, and kept on but was caught by a closing outer rival passing the sixteenth pole to finish with place. KATIESDREAMGIRL trailed in the two path, was ridden around the turn and floated out to the six path into the stretch, and was one paced to get up for show. BULLET ON TAP pressed the pace inside of an outer foe from the three path, took a narrow brief lead passing the half and vied while shifting to the rail around the turn, lost the lead nearing the quarter and was urged right handed in the two path at the top of the lane, but yielded passing the eighth pole. BEAUTIFUL STAR chased in the five path, was cued right handed midway around the turn, but was no menace from the seven path in the stretch.
